  "title": "civil engineer",
  "description": "<p>1. Degree in Building/Construction Studies/Civil &amp; Structural Engineering/Geological Science or equivalent</p>\n<p>2. Ensure full adherence to company policies on-site, particularly health and safety standards</p>\n<p>3. Able to manage and control workers and monitor their work closely</p>\n<p>4. Attend project site meetings with the clients, consultants, sub-contractors, suppliers, authorities, etc. and to ensure the smooth progress of the project</p>\n<p>5. Supervise the collection of soil and rock samples and instrument installation works</p>\n<p>6. Prepare reports from fieldwork eg. Borelogs, installation records and daily journals</p>\n<p>7. Co-ordinating with materials suppliers and managing the delivery, quality and installation of materials</p>",
